  "blurb": "A nine-bedroom hillside estate above Bang Po on Koh Samui's north coast, built for large gatherings around two sea-view swimming pools — with a cinema room, games room, fitness room and multiple jacuzzis, ten en-suite bathrooms, and a resident team serving buffet breakfast, so up to eighteen guests can settle in across 1,700 m² of grounds.",
  "detail": "Set on the hills above Bang Po on Koh Samui's northern coast, this nine-bedroom estate is built for large groups who want room to spread out. Every one of the nine bedrooms is finished to master-suite standard with its own bathroom — ten in all — and the villa sleeps up to eighteen, which makes it a natural fit for extended families, wedding parties and milestone celebrations.\n\nTwo swimming pools anchor the grounds, both angled toward panoramic views of the sea and the mountains behind. The shared spaces are generous: a fitness room, a cinema room, a games room with a pool table and a mahjong table, and several jacuzzis set around the terraces. Open-plan living and dining areas run out to the pools behind sliding glass, and a full kitchen serves the whole estate.\n\nA resident team looks after guests throughout the stay, with a multilingual guest manager on hand and buffet breakfast prepared each morning. Massages, babysitting, island tours and car or motorbike rental can all be arranged, and the villa is set up to host events. Bang Po's quiet beach and seafood restaurants are close by, with Mae Nam and Fisherman's Village a short drive along the coast.",
